  "texts": [
    "The current absence of robust AI governance in healthcare places liability on providers and exposes patients to potential harm.",
    "To mitigate these risks, healthcare institutions should demand clear protocols and comprehensive disclosures from AI developers and EHR vendors, detailing when, where, how, and why AI is used, along with the specific features involved.",
    "Clinician leadership is vital in navigating these challenges.",
    "As advocates for patient welfare, clinicians must actively guide the ethical integration of AI into clinical practice by championing the development of local AI governance frameworks that ensure AI systems are deployed safely and equitably.",
    "Developing such governance requires collaboration among vendors, medical institutions, IRBs, government agencies, patient advocacy groups, and licensing organizations to foster large-scale educational initiatives that enhance AI literacy among the public and clinicians."
  ],
